&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At first glance I would suspect &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11912&quot; title=&quot;reduce number of OST objects created per MDS Sequence&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11912&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11912&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; as the culprit, since it is changing OST object allocation to stress test that code in autotest (this would be much less of an issue in production).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="367946" author="adilger" created="Fri, 31 Mar 2023 00:46:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sebastien, did this happen on a filesystem with fscrypt enabled?  I&apos;m wondering if it failed due to a lack of xattr space for holding 2000 stripes, or if it is just a race condition?  I haven&apos;t seen it before. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
